Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.59,0:00:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to Dr. David Hawkins Sedona 2002\Nseries, The Way to God. Lecture 1,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.00,0:00:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Causality: The Ego's Foundation.\NOriginally presented January 19th, 2002
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.11,0:00:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,at the Sedona Creative Life Center.\NSo I'm very pleased to start with you a
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.52,0:00:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,series of 12 lectures. The last time I\Ndid 12 lectures was back in the early
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.16,0:00:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,80s. And those were 12 uh 12 visits with\Nthe good doctor is what they the way
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.84,0:00:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,they titled them. And the that had to do\Nwith the application of our research on
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.48,0:00:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the nature of consciousness as it\Napplied to various illnesses. So each of
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.48,0:01:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,those 12 tapes applied to a different\Nthing such as heart disease or
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.35,0:01:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,depression or anxiety.\NThis series um the research has
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.24,0:01:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,considerably advanced over the last 20\Nyears.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.76,0:01:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,uh power versus force was preceded by\Ngood 10 years of research and um
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.20,0:01:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,um to\Nmake sure that it met the scientific
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.56,0:01:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,criteria of today's world I went to the\Nbother of getting a PhD
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.11,0:01:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,so as to give it greater academic\Ncredence.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.15,0:01:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I got a PhD at age 65\Nand
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.07,0:01:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and however my PhD didn't come out till\Nabout a month after the book was
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.07,0:01:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,published. So they said so we put the\NPhD on the front. I says no you better
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.75,0:01:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,wait until I get it.\NSo the first edition of power versus
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.56,0:02:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,just said MD and then a month later I\Ngot the PhD. So now it says MD/PhD which
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.60,0:02:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought would impress the world and\Ngive it greater firepower
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.08,0:02:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,because at that time I thought the first\Nsignificant review of the work would be
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.76,0:02:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,in brainmind bulletin and which it was\Nand it got a very positive review and
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.72,0:02:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,resulted in it being published in other\Ncountries.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.64,0:02:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So the research is of course has gone\Nconsiderably further. The purpose of
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.84,0:02:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,power versus force was to go from the\Nfamiliar linear world
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.84,0:02:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and provide a context in which you could\Nmove into the less familiar nonlinear
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.08,0:02:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,with some degree of comfort that you're\Nnot moving into the purely mystical
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.95,0:02:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,imaginary.\NSo I was presenting it from the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.44,0:02:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,viewpoint of what I considered the\Naverage intelligent reader who's also
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.48,0:03:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,interested in spirituality.\Nand who is focused on the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.95,0:03:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,parameter the leading edge of advanced\Ntheoretical physics which is stuck right
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.48,0:03:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,now because it can't get beyond the this\Nblock between the linear and the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.15,0:03:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,nonlinear domain. It's gone about as far\Nas it can go in the linear domain.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.31,0:03:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Um so I helped I was hoping to enlarge\Nthe paradigm of reality of science
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.15,0:03:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,so that the intelligent reader\Nyou know could comprehend the work and
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.44,0:03:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,say ha there must be something uh in the\Nnonlinear domain that we should be
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.64,0:03:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,looking at. So that was that purpose.\NThe purpose of power versus
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.87,0:03:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,was to take us from the familiar\Num the Newtonian paradigm of reality
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.51,0:03:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and prepare us that there is evidence\Nevidence of the reality of the nonlinear
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.40,0:04:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's the great learning block.\Nthe uh intellectuals uh at the present
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.92,0:04:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,time the sort of this almost like a\Npolitical shift in psychiatry for
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.20,0:04:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,instance in which they constantly use\Nthe word evidence-based evidence-based
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.91,0:04:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,so is anything having to do with the\Nnature of man is dead now and we only
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.84,0:04:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,talk about white mice levers and doses\Nof meds and neurotransmitters there's no
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.00,0:04:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,human attached anymore no mention\Nanything human is law because it has to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.96,0:04:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,be evidence-based.\NWell, the purpose of power versus force
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.44,0:04:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,was evidence-based. Evidence-based.\NSo, as you see that scale of
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.60,0:04:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness which has become\Nrelatively well known and has been
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.91,0:04:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,reprinted in many many other books and\Ncited in many references and is
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.96,0:04:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,relatively well known. What I tried to\Ndo was present evidence-based
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.63,0:05:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,documentation of the reality of the\Nnonlinear domain and provide some kind
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.32,0:05:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,of signpost so that the unfamiliar could\Nbe approached without undue anxiety.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.16,0:05:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,People who think the only world is the\Nintellectual world of logic or the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.36,0:05:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,material world are rather frightened of\Nanything that that goes beyond that par
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.80,0:05:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,their paradigm. It has to do with\Nparadigm anxiety. That there's anything
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.28,0:05:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,real that is beyond the science's\Ncapacity to measure is rather scary to
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.12,0:05:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,many people. And it uh and they\Nviferously get on television. You'll see
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.08,0:05:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,them at night, you know, trying to uh\Nprove that near-death experiences are
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.80,0:05:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,all due to brain physiology and God is\Nprobably just a nucleus and
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.52,0:05:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,hypothalammus somewhere\Ntrying to keep keep reality confined
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.40,0:06:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,into this box of the logical\Nuncomfortable
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.24,0:06:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,uh and there are there's some people\Nwhose life is uh devoted to knocking you
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.91,0:06:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,know knocking anything beyond the\Nordinary paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.03,0:06:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So power versus force was then the\Nintroduction to the material and uh the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.80,0:06:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,thing that was interesting about it is\Nthat we learned that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.88,0:06:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,uh you can't use ordinary mechanical\Ninstruments when you're dealing with a
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.91,0:06:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,nonlinear. The nonlinear has to do with\Nwith life itself constantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.24,0:06:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, it would seem obvious that\Nthe measuring instrument of that domain
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.84,0:06:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,would be a living thing. In this case, a\Nhuman being and the response of that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.96,0:06:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,human being to the field of\Nconsciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.68,0:06:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Once in a while I get a letter from\Nreaders says, can't you somehow do this
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.03,0:06:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,electronically?\NThat's missing the point altogether. No,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.72,0:07:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,you cannot do that electronically.\NNor would I have any interest in doing
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.63,0:07:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,it because that is a different world.\NThe electronically recordable world is
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.28,0:07:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the Newtonian paradigm of reality which\Naccording to our calibrated levels of
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.72,0:07:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness stops at 499.\NSo we can follow the greatest scientific
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.24,0:07:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,minds in history, Newton and uh Freud\Nand Einstein
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.91,0:07:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and we\Npush the limits of the scientific
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.03,0:07:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,logical mind. And on our scale of\Nconsciousness of which most people
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.84,0:07:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,they're familiar the 499 is is pretty\Nmuch the edge of
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.44,0:07:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,uh the Newtonian paradigm and you'll\Nfind a lot of very advanced theor uh
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.80,0:07:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,scientific thesis etc doctrines and uh\Nbodies of knowledge stop at 499.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.31,0:08:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's amazing how over the centuries so\Nmany Sir Francis Bacon so many of them
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.44,0:08:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,stop at $499. First I thought I'm making\Na mistake here. And how can they all be
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.91,0:08:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,$4.99\Nand there's some I couldn't believe were
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.52,0:08:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,$4.99. Like Einstein I said no he's got\Nto be more than 54.99.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.56,0:08:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh but no it was $4.99. So that's pretty\Nmuch the level at which we begin to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.75,0:08:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,merge emerge into a different paradigm\Nof reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.84,0:08:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,power versus force took us then from the\NNewtonian into the nonlinear from the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.00,0:08:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,linear domain to the nonlinear.\NYou see if we use language that is not
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.00,0:08:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,religiously historically loaded uh you\Nget a wider audience people who don't
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.83,0:08:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,have you know if you mention it\Nspiritual or religious terms if you
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.12,0:08:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,start dealing in Sanskrit terms a number\Nof people will leave the audience
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.83,0:09:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,because for one reason or another so I\Nhave tried to stick with primarily
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.95,0:09:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,common wording and uh So the world of\Nfamiliarity, America calibrates right
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.44,0:09:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,now at 421. 421.\NThat's the intellect. The 400s are the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.39,0:09:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,intellect.\NSo anybody who's reasonably
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.32,0:09:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,intellectually curious would find the\Nwork interesting and it would lead them
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.04,0:09:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,to the door of a new discovery.\Nright in the beginning I want to correct
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.83,0:09:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of a misconception that may have\Narisen and um and it also has to do with
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.12,0:09:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the um advancement of my own\Nconsciousness and understanding. Um we
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.88,0:09:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of developed a a calibrated map of\Nconsciousness at which 200 was a
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.24,0:09:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,critical level.\NWe said that everything above, we found
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.16,0:10:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that everything above 200, everything\Nthat's true, everything that's valid,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.48,0:10:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,everything that's pro-life,\Neverything that's spiritually um whole
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.00,0:10:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,goes from 200 up and makes you go\Nstrong. Everything below 200 makes you
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.16,0:10:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,go weak.\NUm, and it goes all the way down to the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.16,0:10:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,bottom. So the scale of consciousness\Nwas the very top was the thousand Jesus
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.32,0:10:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Christ, Krishna, Buddha, the great\Navatars that have set the paradigm of
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.92,0:10:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual reality for thousands of years\Ncalibrated at a thousand. And at that
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.83,0:10:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,time we discovered by asking that the\Nhuman nervous system cannot tolerate an
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.20,0:10:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,energy a spiritual energy beyond a\Nthousand. And those of you who've gone
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.60,0:10:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,into very advanced states of\Nconsciousness will remember up to 600 is
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.39,0:10:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,extremely pleasant. In the high 500s is\Nit gets ecstatic.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.72,0:10:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh everything is incredibly beautiful.\NSound is crystalline and pure. Uh
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.60,0:11:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a total oneness to everything.\NEverything happens by um synchronicity.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.36,0:11:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If you think salt, somebody says, "Would\Nyou like some salt?"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.00,0:11:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a marvelous world. You can leave in\Nthe high 500s. You can walk out the door
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.16,0:11:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,without a nickel in your pocket and no\Nfood and everything will be provided.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.24,0:11:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've done it. I walked out without\Nanything.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.20,0:11:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And uh just as you think, gosh, I can\Nshow you a snack. A friend of yours
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.16,0:11:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,says, I'm going for breakfast. Got to\Ntake you after breakfast. It just
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.56,0:11:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,happens that way. And you can go for\Nmonths without anything at all. So the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.88,0:11:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,high 500s are the world of the\Nsynchronous, miraculous, harmonious.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.60,0:11:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an exquisite world.\Nuh many gurus uh I would say the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.12,0:11:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,majority that the world considers to be\Ngurus are in the mid to high 500s
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.36,0:11:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,um over 540 as you remember is uh\Nunconditional love.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.04,0:12:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So a true guru people say what's a true\Nguru a true guru we and we asked
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.76,0:12:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,kinesiology is what has to calibrate\Nover 540 unconditional love. Um
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.83,0:12:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,so that brings us up to 600. At 600 the\Nthe ride up to 600 is hard work in the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.72,0:12:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,beginning but after a while it becomes\Nuh in intensely inspired and it takes on
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.88,0:12:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,an energy of its own. Um\Nand the movement the spiritual movement
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.12,0:12:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,continues of its own valition you might\Nsay. It's like the spiritual energy gets
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.16,0:12:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is so strong that it now takes over the\Nwhole process.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.44,0:12:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and you become more of a witness of it.\NAnd at 600
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.68,0:12:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,um one reaches a state that the world\Ncalls enlightened in which
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.20,0:12:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,um you may or may not stay in the world.\NUh you may or may not stay in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.68,0:13:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,At 600 um everything sort of goes into a\Nstate of exquisite bliss and it's very
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.24,0:13:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,difficult to function.\NIt's uh questionable whether or not to
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.56,0:13:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,even breathe. Uh\Num a number of times breathing only
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.12,0:13:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,resumed because somebody insisted on it.\NSo but you didn't need to breathe and
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.16,0:13:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that state was perfect. The body\Ndisappears as a reality and there is no
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.32,0:13:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,really no reason to continue.\NHowever, there's probably a karmic
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.36,0:13:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,propensity momentum that carries one\Nalong. Uh, in each instant that that
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.68,0:13:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,happened, it was love that uh, it got\Nthe body to breathe again. So, love for
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.44,0:13:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,someone who would have been concerned if\Nthe body stopped breathing. The world
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.20,0:13:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,considers that death and goes into\Ngreater reaction about that. So,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.12,0:13:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody that you care about, you looked\Nat him, you realize he believes in death
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.48,0:13:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and he thinks you're going to be he\Nthinks you're dead and he will now feel
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.16,0:13:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,very bad about that. So you breathe.\NThat's the only reason you breathe but
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.56,0:14:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,because you really don't have to.\NUh so at that point one has really
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.32,0:14:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,entered the nonlinear domain. Uh at um\Nit's 700. We're going to recalibrate.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.72,0:14:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to do redo a few things\Ntoday. Uh we don't have anything from
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.04,0:14:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,700 to a,000. Uh except it just says\Nenlightenment. Actually enlightenment
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.80,0:14:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,starts at 600 and then at 700 uh the\Nreality of the self with a capital S is
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.60,0:14:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,all that is those are the levels of\NRamana Maharshi Nisser Gada Maharaj
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.76,0:14:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,uh uh Swami's number of them uh 800 is\Nquite a high higher level and up to 600
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.04,0:14:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is blissful\Nmaybe even close to 700 but beyond that
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.92,0:14:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,if the the trip the trip at least in\Nthis case was extremely painful.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.07,0:14:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The slightest thing that's out brings a\Nracking pain through the whole nervous
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.16,0:15:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,system and it was horrific at times and\Num by meditation and prayer one gets
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.68,0:15:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,what what the paradox is that's blocking\Nyou. So you learn that what the world
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.32,0:15:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,considers to be the state uh is one of a\Nseries of states.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.88,0:15:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Although it's true enlightenment is at\N600 when most people at 600 don't move
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.83,0:15:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,any further half of them leave the world\Nand don't return
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.60,0:15:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,uh go into retirement uh withdraw from\Nthe world or I suppose they just there
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.92,0:15:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,was nobody around to cajol them into\Nbreathing so they didn't
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.07,0:15:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,uh\Nseldom do they move beyond that um uh uh
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.88,0:15:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,first of all the state is so complete\Nand total and satisfying that it would
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.48,0:15:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Not there would be no thought to move\Nbeyond. There is no beyond. You are
